People are very upset with the country club golf course in the community I'm security for.
Every year during spring they host a HUGE music festival that's absurdly expensive. $600 for a basic ticket that gets you in the door. $6000 to actually reserve a table.
Due to Covid, they have since completely cancelled the event.

People understandably want some refund. The event organizer's response? "Don't we've always had a refund policy for our events. You can easily apply for a refund so long as you've purchased within a week of your refund request."
This event has advertised for months now and most folks reserved their place almost immediately months ago to ensure they got theirs.
Needless to say, people are fuckin' pissed. And they can't do jack shit since even the country club has closed their doors as well. All complaints go straight to the voice mail.
